mobilities of\nthe ions in smooth channels increase to a maximum with ion size and\ndecrease with increasing magnitude of the charge on the ion, while\nuncharged species diffuse much more rapidly and show a monotonic\ndecrease with size. This behavior is related to the characteristics of\nthe fluctuations of the forces on the solute molecules. (53 refs.)},
